Interactive Single Sign-On (SSO) for OPNsense.

Adds OpenID Connect (OIDC), SAML 2.0 and JWT forward-auth as authentication
types under System > Access > Servers. OPNsense acts as a pure Relying Party /
Service Provider: MFA and passkeys live at the Identity Provider
(Authentik, Keycloak, Entra ID, ZItadel, ...).

Features:
  * WebGUI login via an SSO button on the login page (OIDC, SAML and JWT).
  * Captive Portal login via OIDC/SAML.
  * OpenVPN login via the deferred web flow (WEB_AUTH / pending auth).
  * JWT forward-auth: trust a signed JWT from a trusted upstream proxy,
    gated to the proxy's source IP (verified signature, iss/aud/exp).
  * IdP group -> OPNsense group mapping (privileges resolved by the ACL).

The local password path (+ native TOTP) stays active as break-glass.
